l lower bound for makespan is roughly max(FA_makespan + min_FB_chain, FB_makespan_alone). This is complex to compute exactly.\n\nLet me try to construct an improved schedule by reordering jobs to reduce Factory A completion times for jobs with long Factory B sequences.\n\nPLAN_STATE: Baseline makespan is 157. Analyze bottlenecks: MA1 has 39 units total load (bottleneck in FA). Try reordering jobs in Factory A to get earlier completion times for jobs with long Factory B chains (J3, J2, J5). Then schedule Factory B greedily. Target: reduce makespan to ~130-140. Subtask 1: construct improved schedule by trying different job orderings in Factory A (prioritize J1,J2 first since they have shorter FA times), then schedule Factory B. Subtask 2: refine if needed.\n\nNEXT_SUB: {\"id\": 1, \"desc\": \"Construct improved feasible schedule by reordering Factory A jobs to minimize completion times, then greedily schedule Factory B. Try J2,J5 first (shortest FA) to enable early Factory B starts.\", \"p_solve\": 0.55, \"time_budget_s\": 400}",
